1. -- {Welcome to the second chapter. I hope you are warmed up after completing the exercises in the previous chapter.  In this chapter, our focus will be on solving exercises that require us to concentrate on forcing moves. Calculating lines that involve forcing moves is an essential aspect of calculation training.  The ideas presented may vary in their level of obviousness, but accurately calculating the entire variation from start to finish can be quite challenging. Such forcing variations, which encompass a range of tactical patterns, sacrifices, checks, threats, and more, are commonly referred to as combinations in textbooks.   To make the most of this chapter, I encourage you to calculate variations until you arrive at a definite conclusion.} 
*
[Event "?"]
[Site "?"]
[Date "????.??.??"]
[Round "?"]
[White "2) The Magic of Combinations"]
[Black "Gnojek, Petr vs. Mladek, Richard (Czech Extraliga, 2022)"]
[FEN "2r2r2/5pkp/1QB2p2/p3qP2/8/P5P1/2b1P2P/2R2RK1 b - - 0 28"]
