[Result "*"]

1. -- {Welcome to the third chapter. As the name suggests, our focus here is on developing the habit of exploring ideas. It is essential to go beyond our intuition and uncover hidden concepts, both for ourselves and our opponents.  At the beginning of each position, ask yourself this question: Do I have more options than those initially suggested by my intuition? This will encourage you to push yourself further and discover hidden gems within the position. Notably, these hidden ideas may not always be apparent from the start of the exercises. Often, the initial moves of the solution are quite straightforward. However, there comes a moment when you must delve deeper and find that key pivotal idea that can make or break the situation. Being able to identify hidden gems, whether they appear at the start, middle, or end of the variations, is a characteristic of a professional player.} 
*
[Event "?"]
[Site "?"]
[Date "????.??.??"]
