32. Qxc3 {After the smoke has cleared, it is evident that Black stands clearly better. The combination of threats to White's b-pawn and weaknesses on their kingside puts White in a difficult position. At some point, White may have to let go of the b-pawn, and defending the resulting endgame won't be an easy task.} 
