 {There are various decent moves for White after which we can enjoy a clear advantage. But can you find the best one which helps us claim a winning advantage?} 31. Qb3 {A clever move, putting pressure on Black's vulnerable pawn on f7. White also sets up an unavoidable threat, which will be unleashed in the next move.} 
31. Nh7 {31...Bc8could a better way to resist White's threat. Although it does not entirely prevent it.32.Bxe5(32.Nxe5+-also works for White).32...Bxe5(32...Be633.Qb2Bxa234.Bxg7+-Black will be crushed on the dark squares).33.Nxe5Be634.Qb2Bxa2and now White has the strong35.Ng4+-Threatening Nf6+ followed by Nd5+ winning the Queen. If Black defends against it then we can simply recapture on a2 with a winning advantage.} 
32. Nxe5 {Black's Queen is overloaded to the defence of the e5 and f7 pPawns. White exploits this fact at the first opportunity.} 
